				<section>
				  <p> Currently piloting two e-learning solutions for some of our maths courses at HiB:</p>
				  <div class="fragment">
				  <ul>
				    <li>WeBWorK instance (CAA)</li>
				    <li>an Open edX instance (videos and CAA)</li>
				  </ul><br><br>
				  <img width="35%" src="assets/webwork_1.png"> <img width="35%" src="assets/edx_1.png">
				  </div>
				</section>


				<section>
				  <section>
				    <h3> WeBWorK </h3>
				    An open-source online homework system built by MAA <a href="http://webwork.maa.org/">webwork.maa.org</a><br><br>
				    <a href="assets/webwork_1.png">
				      <img width="60%" src="assets/webwork_1.png">
				    </a>
				  </section>

				  <section data-background-video="assets/demo_video_webwork.mp4">
				    <div style="color:white">
				      <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>
				 
				      <div class="transbox">
				      <span style=" -webkit-text-stroke: 1px black; font-size:80%">
				      <p>Used for both obligatory assignments and voluntary exercises</p>
				      <p class="fragment">Possible to give a broad range of problems<br>
					<small>Much more than multiple choice!</small> </p>
				      <p class="fragment">Students have to do pen and paper calculations</p>
				      <p class="fragment">Immediate feedback. Problems are automatically corrected </p>
				      </span>
				      </div>

				    </div>
				  </section>

				  <section>
				    <p>Students can get hints based on answer. Built-in instructor solutions</p>
				    <a href="assets/webwork_prob_2.png">
				      <img width="70%" src="assets/webwork_prob_2.png">
				    </a>
				  </section>

				  <section>
				    Can track each student individually<br><br>
				    <a href="assets/webwork_track_1.png">
				      <img width="100%" src="assets/webwork_track_1.png">
				    </a>
				  </section>

				  <section>
				    <p>Attempted answers give insight into thought process</p>
				    <a href="assets/webwork_track_2.png">
				      <img width="100%" src="assets/webwork_track_2.png">
				    </a>

				  </section> 

				  <section>
				    Possible to have individual tracks through a problem set (adaptive learning)<br>
				    <pre><code class="hljs" data-trim contenteditable>
					if prob_1 not correct, go to prob_1.1. Else prob_2
					</code></pre>
				    <a href="assets/webwork_prob_3.png">
				      <img width="60%" src="assets/webwork_prob_3.png">
				    </a>
				  </section>

				  <section>
				    We are creating our own library of exercises tailored to our students (in Norwegian) <br><br>
				    <a href="assets/webwork_3.png">
				      <img width="80%" src="assets/webwork_3.png">
				    </a>
				  </section>
								  
				  <section>
				    The HiB exercise library.  Hosted on GitHub. <br><br>
				    <a href="assets/webwork_4.png">
				      <img width="60%" src="assets/webwork_4.png">
				    </a>
				  </section>

				  <section>
				    <ul>
				      <li class="fragment grow">Still just a pilot. Only used in a few courses. </li><br>
				      <li>Able to give many more obligatory exercises than before (don't tell the students!)</li><br>
				      <li>Feedback from students very positive (mid-term evaluations and student interviews) </li>
				    </ul>
				    <br><br>
				    <div class="fragment">
				      <p><span style="color:blue"><em>Cannot be more than a supplement to written hand-ins</em></span><br><br>
					<span class="fragment">We combine CAA with good ol' teacher aided assessment. Students must show that they can reason mathematically. </span></p>
				    </div>
				  </section>
				</section>


				<section>
				  <section>
				    <h3> Open edX </h3>
				    <div class="fragment">
				    <p> An open-source MOOC platform built by (among others) MIT and Stanford University. Powers <a href="http://edx.org">edX.org</a></p>
				    <a href="assets/edx_1.png">
				      <img width="60%" src="assets/edx_1.png">
				    </a>
				    </div>
				  </section>
				  <section>
				  We use it for video-based support courses (blended learning)<br><br>
				    <a href="assets/edx_2.png">
				      <img width="80%" src="assets/edx_2.png">
				    </a>
				  </section>
				  <section data-background-video="assets/demo_video.mp4">
				    <div style="color: white;">
				      <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>
				      <div class="transbox">
				      <span style=" -webkit-text-stroke: 1px black; font-size:80%">
				    <p> Students are able to watch and rewatch examples as many times as they like </p>
				    <p class="fragment"> Can slow down or speed up the videos</p>
				    <p class="fragment"> Tracking: Number of times watched; number of attempts at exercises</p>
				      </span>
				      </div>
				    </div>
				  </section>
				  <section>
